        /* Make the course table mobile friendly*/

        @media
        only screen and (max-width: 980px),
        (max-device-width: 980px)  {

        #coursetable { width:100%; }

        /* Force table to not be like tables anymore */
        #coursetable,
        #coursetable thead,
        #coursetable tbody,
        #coursetable th,
        #coursetable td,
        #coursetable tr,
        #requirementstable,
        #requirementstable thead,
        #requirementstable tbody,
        #requirementstable th,
        #requirementstable td,
        #requirementstable tr
        {
        display: block;
        }

        /* Hide table headers (but not display: none;, for accessibility) */
        #coursetable tr th{
        position: absolute;
        top: -9999px;
        left: -9999px;
        }

        #coursetable tr { border: 1px solid #ccc; }

        #coursetable tbody td {
        /* Behave  like a "row" */
        border: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 50%;
        padding-top: 10px;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        #coursetable td:before {
        /* Now like a table header */
        position: absolute;
        /* Top/left values mimic padding */
        top: 10px;
        left: 8px;
        width: 45%;
        padding-right: 10px;
        white-space: nowrap;
        font-weight:bold;
        }

        /*
        Label the data
        */
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(1):before { content: "CRN"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(2):before { content: "Course"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(3):before { content: "Title"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(4):before { content: "Meeting Time"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(5):before { content: "Room"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(6):before { content: "Instructor"; }

        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(8):before { content: "Res Seats"; }
        #coursetable td:nth-of-type(9):before { content: "Prm"; }

<td colspan="13" class="dddefault"><font color="red"><b>Department: Acct &amp; Financial Management : </b>All School of Management courses give preference in registration to BSBA and MGEG students EXCEPT: MGMT 100, MGMT 203, ACFM 220, ACFM 261, ACFM 351, ACFM 377, and GLBM 300. Non-majors should waitlist for all other courses. Waitlisted students will be placed into open seats following the last day of course registration. No further actions are necessary in the meantime. </font></td>

<td colspan="13" class="dddefault"><font color="red"><b>Department: History : </b>Introductory (100-level) history courses are intended for first- and second-year students. Third- and fourth-year students will be admitted to these courses only at the discretion of the instructor.

IP Courses (UNIV 200) count for History credits.</font></td>
</tr>

<td colspan="13" class="dddefault"><font color="red"><b>Department: Markets, Innovation &amp; Design : </b>All School of Management courses give preference in registration to BSBA and MGEG students EXCEPT: MGMT 100, MGMT 203, ACFM 220, ACFM 261, ACFM 351, ACFM 377, and GLBM 300. Non-majors should waitlist for all other courses.  Waitlisted students will be placed into open seats following the last day of course registration.  No further actions are necessary in the meantime. </font></td>

<tr align="left">
<td class="dddefault">16767</td>
<td nowrap="nowrap" class="dddefault">MIDE 300 01</td>
<td class="dddefault">Markets,<br> Innovation &amp;<br> Design</td>
<td nowrap="" class="dddefault">
